  stickyNoteInfos:
  - title: 'Spawn Context Options :'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 1268
      y: -944
      width: 348
      height: 143
    contents: "By selecting the Spawn Context Block (the green square box filled
      with blocks), you can change the loop duration, loop count, and delay between
      the loops.\r\n\r\nIn the Inspector Window, we change the \u201CLoop Duration\u201D
      to constant and \u201CDelay Mode.\u201D\r\nWith this, we were able to adjust
      the loop duration and delay.\r\n"
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: 'Spawn Burst :'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 1663
      y: -759
      width: 404
      height: 164
    contents: "We can have a constant spawn rate of particles, but in this case,
      we decided to use a \u201Csingle burst.\u201D\r\n\r\nThis node is responsible
      for \u201Cbursting\u201D a constant number of particles in one frame at the
      start (+ delay) of each loop.\r\n\r\nWith each new loop, several particles
      are generated based on the \u201Cloop index.\u201D\r\n"
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: 'Spawn State :'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 756
      y: -839
      width: 259
      height: 205
    contents: "While in the \u201Cspawn context,\u201D you can have access to valuable
      information like the loop index, spawn count, loop state, loop duration, etc.\r\n\r\nJust
      press the Space Bar and search for \u201Cspawn state.\u201D\r\nNotice that
      you can reduce the size of the node so that it shows only the connected pin
      by clicking the arrow in the upper-right corner of any block.\r\n"
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 3
  - title: 'Setting Spawn Event Attributes:'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 1663
      y: -494
      width: 403
      height: 156
    contents: "We can set attributes (lifetime, color, alpha, etc.) in the \u201CSpawn
      Context\u201D. \r\nThe values are global to the Spawn Context and can be \u201Cinherited\u201D
      later on by the particle in the \u201CInitialize Context.\u201D\r\n\r\nIn this
      example, we set the \u201Clifetime\u201D to be equal to the loop duration +
      delay so that our particle's lifetime matches the loop duration.\r\n\r\nWe
      also get a random color for each new loop.\r\n"
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: 'Inherit Source Color:'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 1688
      y: 227
      width: 469
      height: 117
    contents: "While this block seems different from \u201CSet Lifetime,\u201D it's
      actually doing the same.\r\n\r\nWhen clicking on it, in the inspector, we get
      access to \u201CSource attribute data.\u201D By changing this option to \u201CSource,\u201D
      we can directly \u201Cinherit\u201D the data from the Spawn Context.\r\n"
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 2
  categories: []
  uiBounds:
    serializedVersion: 2
    x: -4
    y: -1003
    width: 2186
    height: 2462
